      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments conducted at 5 flow-speed combinations spanning 2–6 L/min and 2000–3500 RPM using bovine blood at 37°C. Test conditions documented per ASTM F1841. Conditions match the COU operating range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index must agree with experimental measurements within 15% across all 5 operating points at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements. Mean absolute error of 8.3% observed across all 5 operating points. Maximum deviation of 13.7% at the highest flow-speed combination. Acceptance criterion met."
