      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) must be directly linked to the decision criterion (RH < 1) at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which maps directly to the relative hemolysis index (RH) used as the acceptance criterion. Shear stress fields provide mechanistic insight. QoI relevance fully established with quantitative linkage to decision threshold."
